                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1121 Blodgett, Walton/180: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain (<persName type="from"
                            >Bowers</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-01-29T14:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 29, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 29—11:07 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>14. Your telegram of January 27, 3 p.m. Just saw Foreign Minister. Papers from
                    Palma de Mallorca arrived with condition of prisoners described as excellent.
                    Minister made engagement in my presence to see President Supreme Court to
                    arrange and to recommend pardon so Council Ministers can act Friday.
                    Unprecedented rapidity in pardon case. Vitally important that press and Congress
                    keeps hands off.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
